Feel like you should be posting your content across all social media channels?

Well, you’re right. You should.

But there is nuance to it.

Every channel works differently.

And in most cases, you need to “work” a platform to actually grow there.

For example: If you just post to LinkedIn and you aren’t present there.

Don’t expect your content to perform well. Or to get customers directly from posting content.

But, if someone finds you on TikTok, and then navigates to LinkedIn because that is their preferred platform. You’ll have a presence there when they search for you.

So just be very intentional about where and why you’re posting on a given channel so that your expectations and level of effort match up.
